FBIS3-31732 "dreeu036_i_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-036 Document Type:Daily Report 23 Feb 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Swedish UNPROFOR Troops Near Tuzla Injured AU2202181094 Paris AFP in English 1757 GMT 22 Feb 94 AU2202181094 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Stockholm, Feb 22 (AFP) -- Five Swedish UN soldiers were injured Tuesday [22 February] when a grenade struck their tank north of Vares outside Tuzla, northeast Bosnia, the Swedish defence ministry said Tuesday. Four of the the soldiers suffered shrapnel wounds, while one suffered eye injuries, Swedish defence ministry officials said. They were transported by helicopter to a Norwegian field hospital outside Tuzla. It is not yet known who was responsible for the attack. Both Serbs and Moslems hold positions in the area. It also uncertain whether the tank was targeted or hit by accident, Swedish defence ministry officials said.
